tweet: You are the peace keepers, the shield for the innocent and vulnerable, the guardians standing between us and violence and lawlessness.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: The fallen heroes we remember today all answered the same call of duty to protect and serve. And their hearts were filled with the same selfless courage… and love. For “no greater love has a man than this, that he should lay down his life for his friends.” #PoliceWeek

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: This year alone, we’ve seen attacks that have claimed the lives of 28 heroes.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: But as all of you know – and as this day of remembrance so vividly reminds us – there is much work to be done to ensure the safety and security of our law enforcement. #PoliceWeek

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: We are with you.  We stand with you.  And we will always give those who serve on the Thin Blue Line of law enforcement the HONOR and RESPECT you earn every single day!

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Last year, @POTUS Trump and I were honored to stand before this extraordinary gathering – and the President promised that in this administration, “we will always support the incredible men and women of law enforcement” – and that is precisely what President Trump has done.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: It’s National Police Week. I am deeply humbled to join so many courageous men and women of law enforcement – and especially the families of our fallen – at the 37th Annual National Peace Officers’ Memorial Service. #PoliceWeek

tweet: Honored to join @POTUS, the law enforcement community, & families of our fallen for the annual #PeaceOfficersMemorialDay service today. Our courageous law enforcement officers sacrifice every day to keep our communities safe. WATCH LIVE:  https://t.co/UUeMY4KUw5 #PoliceWeek

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: As it has been in the past, so it shall be in the future: America stands with Israel.  https://t.co/OI6PbAwXfA

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: As we look at Israel today, it is extraordinary to behold all the progress she has made, and the example that she sets. Today, the modern State of Israel is not only 70 years old – Israel is 70 years strong.  https://t.co/8z1p2dW23f

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Israel will go from strength to strength – and her first 70 years will just be a glimpse of what’s to come – and the United States and Israel will meet our glorious future together.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: And we stand with Israel because that’s what Americans have always done – for in the story of Israel, we see the power of faith, and the promise of hope.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: We stand with Israel because her cause is our cause, her values are our values, and her fight is our fight.   We stand with Israel because we believe in right over wrong, good over evil, and liberty over tyranny.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: And so today, let me assure you all… the United States of America will never allow Iran to obtain a nuclear weapon – that is our solemn promise to Israel and to the world!

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: As @POTUS said, the Iran deal “didn’t bring calm, it didn’t bring peace, and it never will.” In fact, Iran’s unprecedented missile attacks on Israel last week only confirmed the President’s decision, and this dangerous act of aggression only strengthened our resolve.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: By finally recognizing Jerusalem as Israel’s capital, the United States has chosen fact over fiction – and fact is the only true foundation for a just and lasting peace. And as @POTUS Trump made clear this morning, “our greatest hope is for peace.”

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Just as President Truman made history then, @POTUS Trump has made history now — thanks to @POTUS’ leadership, almost exactly 70 years to the minute since the rebirth of the Jewish State, the American Embassy officially opened in Jerusalem, the capital of the State of Israel!

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: It is my distinct honor to accept this unique recognition, from the State of Israel, for the greatest defender of the Jewish State ever to sit in the Oval Office. I know the President is honored by this expression of the high esteem and great affection from the people of Israel.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: It is deeply humbling to stand here with you on this extraordinary day – as we celebrate 70 Years of Israel’s Independence.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: To the graduates of @Hillsdale: You are beginning your careers at a time of a growing American economy and restored American stature at home and abroad. Faith in America is rising once again.  https://t.co/WK84wMJcWz

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Congratulations to the @Hillsdale College Class of 2018.   Right after WE get done making this nation great again, I know YOUR generation will make America greater than ever before.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: The most heroic acts & greatest feats aren’t the stuff of headlines & fame. They’re actually the daily choices that you make & the habits you’ve already begun to form.  Ultimately, whether you renew America comes down to whether you live what you have learned at @Hillsdale.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Your education in the liberal arts has empowered you to conserve the foundations of our freedom… and you are now uniquely suited – and I believe you are uniquely called – to renew the fabric of our national life.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: I encourage you to take your deepest-held convictions into every facet of your life – and add your voices, and your values, to this new American awakening.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Faith has always been the wellspring of hope for millions of Americans, and from our Founding, faith has been the foundation of our freedom, and religion essential to our republic.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Religion in America isn’t receding – just the opposite. Faith is gaining new life with every passing day.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: The percentage of Americans who live out their religion on a weekly basis – by praying, going to church, and reading and believing in the Bible – has remained remarkably consistent over the decades, even as the population of the United States has grown by leaps and bounds.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: We live in a time when traditional values, even religious conviction, are increasingly marginalized by a secular popular culture – a time when it's become acceptable, even fashionable, to malign religious belief. I still believe with all my heart that FAITH in America is rising.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Faith in America is rising again because @POTUS Trump and our entire administration have been advancing the very principles that you learned here in the halls of @Hillsdale College.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: Here at home, businesses large and small are growing again – more than 3.1 million new jobs, unemployment at a 17-year low, and the best news of all for you new graduates today, there are more job openings across America than any time in the history of this country.

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: On the world stage, you’ve seen America embracing our role as leader of the free world – with action just this week regarding Iran, North Korea, and on Monday, America will lead the world again when we open our new Embassy in Jerusalem, the capital of Israel!

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
tweet: The America that awaits your energies and ambitions is experiencing a new era of opportunity and optimism.  You are beginning your careers at a time of a growing American economy and a restored American stature at home and abroad. And faith in America is rising again!

name: Vice President Mike Pence Archived
